Hello! We have 5 bedrooms available in our huge 3 floor, 7 bedroom, 2.5 bathroom house. They will be available 8/1 and 9/1 depending on the room. There is a 1 year lease. First, last, security due at lease signing, and credit check. Bad credit? Ok with a cosigner. Only 1 person per/room. If a couple wants to move in and take another room to use as an office/studio/etc that is ok.
//A little about the house. There is 1 bedroom on the first floor, 3 on the second floor and 3 on the third. Rent $ ranges from $700-925, varying by room size, all utilities included for a year. We just split internet which which is extremely cheap. No cable by choice, but if people want it, they can get it. Street parking with permit. There are 2 parking spots available for a monthly fee in the lot out back, please inquire. Washer/dryer in basement (NOT coin op, included with utilities). Lots of storage in basement. Please see attached pictures for rooms, prices, and size. Some furniture will be going, not sure what yet.
//The house is located a 5 minute walk to Sullivan Square T stop, orange line. In a pretty quiet neighborhood. Were looking for responsible, cleanly, respectful, easy going, down to earth people. Who are ok with not having our house be "the" party house, and having people in/out like grand central station. We love to hang, and love get-to-gethers, but in moderation.
//The kitchen is huge! Tons of counter space and cabinets on both sides. Dishwasher, garbage disposal, 2 sinks, 2 fridges, a wine cooler/fridge built in, and a small utility closet. All new stainless steel appliances.
//The living room is a good size with French doors that open up into the dinning room. Extremely open and very sunny.
//Pets - cat is ok if friendly to other cats, if you keep the litter clean and swept off the floor. There is an extra $35 fee per month on top of rent if you have a cat. Litter boxes not welcome in common areas besides bathrooms.
//A bit about us: Marie: I am the one working with the landlord to fill this house, and will be answering replies, and initial interviewing/showing. I am a professional gal in my 30`s, I work as the print production designer at a travel company. I do have a cat that lives with me. He mostly just sloth`s around my room, but does roam the house. I love music, travel, art and all things creative. I spend a lot of time during the week working and week day evenings for me are quiet due to my work schedule, I prefer keep my play time on the weekends and away from home 90% of the time, and we both prefer housemates that keep the majority of their play time away as well :)
//Cedric: in my twenties, recently move out here from NYC, work for a biomedical company, I`m very neat, respectful, friendly and in all easygoing, I like traveling, music, sport arenas, road trips, movies etc, I tend to stay a lot in my room watching movies.the house so far is made of loving, neat and easygoing house mates.
Tell us a bit about yourself. Please don`t just ask if the room is still available. We want to know, how old you are. What you do for work, how long you`ve been there. What do you do for fun/down time, hobbies, interests etc. Please EMAIL inquiries here or TEXT. Please do not call if you want to hear from me promptly.
